# AI Starter Kit - Environment Variables Example
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development

# =============================================================================
# CONVEX (Auto-generated by `npx convex dev`)
# =============================================================================

# Your Convex deployment URL
# This is automatically created when you run `npx convex dev`
# DO NOT manually set this - let Convex generate it
NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud

# =============================================================================
# CONVEX ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (Set via `npx convex env set`)
# =============================================================================

# These are NOT stored in .env.local - they're stored in Convex cloud
# Set them using the commands below:

# Better Auth Secret (required)
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
# Command: npx convex env set BETTER_AUTH_SECRET $(openssl rand -base64 32)
# BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=your-generated-secret-here

# Site URL (required)
# For local development: http://localhost:3000
# For production: https://yourdomain.com
# Command: npx convex env set SITE_URL http://localhost:3000
# SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL: ADDITIONAL SERVICES
# =============================================================================

# If you add email service (future)
# EMAIL_FROM=noreply@yourdomain.com
# EMAIL_PROVIDER_API_KEY=your-api-key

# If you add OAuth providers (future)
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret
# GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your-github-client-id
# GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your-github-client-secret

# If you add analytics (optional)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID=your-analytics-id

# If you add error tracking (optional)
# SENTRY_DSN=your-sentry-dsn

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env.local:
#    cp .env.example .env.local

# 2. Run Convex dev (this creates NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL automatically):
#    npx convex dev

# 3. Set Convex environment variables:
#    npx convex env set BETTER_AUTH_SECRET $(openssl rand -base64 32)
#    npx convex env set SITE_URL http://localhost:3000

# 4. Start the development server:
#    pnpm run dev

# =============================================================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
# =============================================================================

# For production, use DIFFERENT secrets:
# npx convex env set BETTER_AUTH_SECRET $(openssl rand -base64 32) --prod
# npx convex env set SITE_URL https://yourdomain.com --prod

# And set NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL in your deployment platform (e.g., Vercel):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-prod-deployment.convex.cloud

# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================

# - Never commit .env.local to git (it's in .gitignore)
# - Use different secrets for dev and production
# - Convex env variables are stored securely in Convex cloud, not in .env.local
# - Only NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables are exposed to the browser
# - See docs/SETUP.md for detailed setup instructions
